'''Eduard Campabadal Claros''' (born 26 January 1993) is a [[Spain|Spanish]] professional [[Association football|football]] defender who currently plays for [[Wigan Athletic F.C.|Wigan Athletic]].

==Wigan Athletic==
Campabadal joined [[Wigan Athletic F.C.|Wigan Athletic]] in July 2012 after being released by [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2175635/Barcelona-duo-join-Wigan-Athletic.html | title=Barcelona pair join Wigan as Martinez signs Campabadal and Guillermo | work=Mail Online | publisher=Associated Newspapers Ltd | date=18 July 2012 | accessdate=20 May 2013}}</ref> He made his debut for the first team on 19 May 2013 on the final day of the [[Premier League]] season in a 2<U+2013>2 draw against [[Aston Villa F.C.|Aston Villa]].

